name: DP Conway
commentary: Shami breaches the defences of Conway. That's his 100th IPL wicket. Nice and full, angling in from round the stumps, seaming in at Conway who aims for a booming drive and misses. Bowled through the gate. The ball clatters into middle stump

name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: Joseph misses the yorker, but is still a hard-to-hit middle-stump full-toss, which is spliced into the hands of long-on. Is that a high full-toss? Gaikwad thinks so. <s>Gaikwad has asked for a review</s>. The umpires converge and ask for a review. The ball dips below the waist and therefore Gaikwad has to go. End of a terrific innings from Gaikwad. He falls eight short of a century

name: MM Ali
commentary: Rashid strikes back, Moeen has nicked off. Easier decision for umpire Khalid. Rashid takes this wrong'un away from the left-handed Moeen who throws his bat at ball once again. He edges it behind to Saha who clings onto the catch

name: BA Stokes
commentary: Rashid takes out both Moeen and Stokes. Pushed through flatter and quicker, skids away outside off from over the stumps. Stokes chops at it and edges it behind to Saha who makes this low catch look ridiculously easy

name: AT Rayudu
commentary: Maiden IPL wicket for Josh Little. Rayudu dashes out of the crease, swings for the hills once again, but does not lay bat on ball. Little cranks it up to almost 140ks and nails the stumps

name: S Dube
shortText: c Rashid Khan b Mohammed Shami
commentary: throat-high short ball angling across Dube. He goes for another hook, this time he holes out to Rashid Khan at deep square leg. Another mis-hit and this goes to the fielder. Dube has been put out of his misery

name: RA Jadeja
commentary: Joseph goes for the yorker, marginally misses it, but has Jadeja holing out to deep midwicket. Mighty full on the pads, Jadeja picks it up and picks out the fielder on the boundary

name: WP Saha
commentary: wicket number no. 1 for Hangargekar. In his first over. Outswinger from the hand, moves away. It is widish to start off with it. Saha still flashes at it, gets a thick edge, which settles with deep third this time

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: this one is an easy catch for eep midwicket. Tries the pull but it goes off the toe end of the bat as he is dragging it from wide outside off. Taken at deep midwicket this time

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: oh not the best delivery to get a wicket. Short and wide, Sudharsan looks for the cut, but it is too wide for him, and he just toe-ends it to Dhoni

name: HH Pandya
commentary: Jadeja has not given Pandya anything so far. So he goes down to look to sweep. Jadeja keeps doing what he has been doing. Look to hit top of off. Pandya sweeps from around off, misses it completely, and Jadeja hits somewhere near the top of off

name: V Shankar
commentary: big wicket. Looks like a slower ball. Shankar is looking to go in the air and down the ground. Gets the right length, right in the slot, but he seems to have bowled a slower ball. Shankar ends up toe-ending it for a catch half way between mid-off and long-off. CSK still alive

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Southee has the last laugh as this good length ball angles down leg and Singh can't help himself but try to flick it fine. This time it gets an edge and Gurbaz moves to his left to gobble it up. Singh's cameo is over, but it has given the Kings a positive start

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: S Dhawan
commentary: through him - and Dhawan's captaincy curse continues where he is yet to get a fifty after being (C).- Good length ball on leg and skidding straight through. Hits Dhawan's pad en route to the stumps. Dhawan goes for 40 with a strike rate of 137

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: PBB Rajapaksa
commentary: going, going, not gone! Rajapaksa fifty and out. Fullish ball ball around leg and Rajapaksa took one step down the track before trying to tonk it over long on. The connection is decent but not good enough to clear long on. Rinku gets under it and takes a regulation catch a few metres inside the crease. But he's done his job

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: JM Sharma
commentary: too much experience in Southee and he produces another good ball after being hit for a six. Slower ball just outside off stump. Jitesh loses his shape while trying to slog it over the leg side, but this sliced shot produces a simple catch for Umesh at short third

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Sikandar Raza
commentary: simple for Rana running square from point. Narine with a bit more air on off. Raza backs away and tries to go inside out. Ends up slicing it high for an easy dismissal. KKR quietly pulling things back at the death

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: SM Curran

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: M Shahrukh Khan

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Mandeep Singh
commentary: Arshdeep strikes first ball! He is celebrating with his arms wide, and with half a sprint down long leg. Good pace and bounce from him though. H pitched it about middle and off, as the ball angled across, and rose rather sharply on off stump. Mandeep pulled, but the extra bounce got him. Straight into deep square leg's hands

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Rahmanullah Gurbaz
commentary: Ellis pings off stump! This time Ellis had good pace on ball, changing up after that slower delivery last ball. Gurbaz, again trying to be adventurous, makes some room, and also skips out of the crease. He hacks at this good length ball on off - rather it was on the shorter side of a length - and missed, as the stumps lit up

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: AS Roy
shortText: c Sikandar Raza b Arshdeep Singh
commentary: spooned to midwicket! Arsh gets two in this over. I think the extra bounce came into play again, and so did his pace. Another short delivery from Arsh, and this one's line was a bit wide of off, much further away from the middle-stump line he cramped Anukul with previous ball. Anukul pulled, but found the fielder, who didn't have to move at all

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: VR Iyer
commentary: ramped to point! Another bouncer from Arsh earns him a wicket. The bounce was a bit too much for Iyer to handle. Arsh banged it in short around off, with Iyer almost leaping a little to get on top of it. But he ended up half-ramping it - and without any control - to point

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: N Rana
commentary: slashed straight to point! Raza is relieved after going for some runs in his first two overs. That was there to be hit, but Rana ended up gifting the fielder an easy catch. Short and slightly wide of off, as Rana went hard at that only to end up walking back. So the time-out breaks his momentum

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: RK Singh
commentary: strikes first ball, just like Arshdeep! Rinku goes after the legspinner right away, but finds deep midwicket. Chahar bowls on a length on off, but it is the wrong 'un. It turns away from Rinku's arc, as he looks to slog sweep. Instead, the ball ends up landing right into the fielder's lap

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: AD Russell
commentary: finds deep midwicket! Could be exactly the wrong time for KKR, given there is rain around. Curran went short again, except that this one was an offcutter, which rose sharply after pitching middle and leg, while also angling across. Russell swat-pulled but only off the higher side of the bat

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: SN Thakur

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: SP Narine

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KL Rahul
commentary: slower ball trap works! 118 kph delivery back of a length on the legs, flicks this loosely to deep backward square leg where Axar gleefully takes the catch five yards inside the rope at chest height.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KR Mayers
commentary: goodness what turn! Axar digs this into the pitch on a good length on fifth stump, Mayers goes to cut and the ball jacknifes back into off stump. If that happened on a highway there'd be a 20-car pileup and three lanes of traffic closed while the police investigate the cause of the crash. Extraordinary delivery.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: DJ Hooda
commentary: flighted a lot more on a full length on fourth stump at 81 kph, Hooda is through the shot too early and skies the drive to Warner at long-off. He waits under it for a simple catch taken on his haunches seven yards in from the rope.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KH Pandya

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MP Stoinis
commentary: length ball angled across sixth stump at 134 kph, Stoinis chases at this flat-footed and slices a thick edge through to the keeper at waist height. Khaleel charges off and celebrates wildly like a man who definitely and most certainly did not drop a different batter on 14 who went on to make 73...

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: N Pooran
commentary: fullish length ball outside off, smokes a drive flat to Prithvi in the ring at extra cover. He catches it in self-preservation at waist height. Absolute howitzer off the bat of Pooran but he couldn't have picked out Shaw any better.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: A Badoni
commentary: slower length ball on fourth stump, Badoni shuffles across trying to scoop this over fine leg but is thrown off by the lack of pace and it pings the gloves before ballooning to the left of Sarfaraz, who shuffles five yards and reaches forward for a simple take.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: K Gowtham

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: PP Shaw
commentary: bullseye! Wood rattles the off stump wood at 147 kph! Bowled on a good length angled in from wide of the crease, Shaw's feet never move and he flails at this tamely. He's beaten badly and the bails go flying.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: DA Warner
commentary: slower ball lands full on seventh stump, Warner miscues a drive skying this to long-on. Simple catch taken three yards inside the rope by K Gowtham.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MR Marsh
commentary: double bullseye! Another 147 kph bullet leaves a big dent in off stump about three-quarters of the way up! Marsh shuffled across to cover his stumps and goes for an expansive drive to a ball pitching on fifth stump but is beaten by the sharp inward movement.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: SN Khan
commentary: Sarfaraz can't escape the short ball from Wood! Banged in short at 137 kph, Sarfaraz ducks and almost falls over getting out of the way of the ball... before bizarrely changing his mind in a split second as he's losing his balance and tries to attack this with an uppercut over the keeper. He gets plenty of bat on it, enough for it to sail to deep fine leg who is fielding very straight and takes a chest high catch three yards in from the rope.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: RR Rossouw
commentary: full on leg stump, shuffles well across the stumps and goes to sweep and misses off the pads/shoes, huge lbw shout denied and the ball pops up off a deflection of some kind behind the wicket for a catch claimed by the short fine leg fielder. Looked pretty stone dead live. LSG have gone for a review. Rossouw has started marching off without even waiting for the replays. Nothing on bat or glove on the initial shot but the ball has popped up off the bat of the bat on the follow through in bizarre fashion and a catch was taken by the fielder coming over from short fine leg. We're not even going to get to the ball-tracking for lbw because he's been given out caught.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: R Powell
commentary: 99 kph googly skids on from a good length on fourth stump and zings Powell in front of middle stump on the back foot playing back to punch through midwicket. He read the googly but it just came onto him far quicker than he expected and he's too late getting the bat down. Big lbw shout upheld. Powell marches off without a moment's thought for a review. It was stone dead.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Aman Hakim Khan
commentary: bounced out! Short ball on the stumps at 136 kph, goes to pull and is hustled for pace top edging this high behind the stumps. Keeper Pooran shuffles in front of short fine leg for the take.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: AR Patel
commentary: It's Wood's night for sure! Leg stump half-volley flicked effortlessly but picks out deep square leg. Sub fielder Mankad takes a simple catch at chest height four yards inside the rope. Not as spectacular a delivery as his previous three wicket-taking balls but still effective nonetheless.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Kuldeep Yadav

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: C Sakariya
commentary: Wood has a five-for after making the switch to LSG! Length ball outside leg stump, Sakariya tries to heave this over the leg side but is rushed and it flutters up off the splice of the bat to Krunal at short midwicket inside the ring. Simple catch.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Mukesh Kumar

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: YBK Jaiswal
commentary: holes out to deep square leg! Farooqi has another! Banged into the track on middle and off stump. Jaiswal looks to heave it away but does not quite get hold of it. In fact, he toe-ends it and Mayank does the rest on the fence! Vital wicket for SRH!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: JC Buttler
commentary: cleans him up! Farooqi breaks through! Back of a length delivery at the stumps that skids through and might have just nipped back a shade. Buttler tries to punch on the up but the movement means that he gets a feather of an inside edge that cannons into the top of middle and off stump! Much-needed respite for the Sunrisers Hyderabad!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: SV Samson
commentary: taken brilliantly at deep mid wicket! Slower delivery on a back of a length outside off stump, and this one just sticks in the surface a little. Samson has a swipe at it but is early into the stroke. He shanks it towards deep mid wicket, where Abhishek settles himself, catches it and then tiptoes his way out of trouble beautifully!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: D Padikkal
commentary: cleans him up with a corker! Heat-seeking 149.2 kph missile that hones in on off stump. Padikkal is already hanging back because of the extra pace and is awfully late on the stroke. He jumps up into the air but cannot do anything as the ball whistles past the bat and sends off stump flying!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: R Parag
commentary: taken at short third man! Natarajan gets Parag! Back of a length delivery outside off stump. Parag has a hack across the line but the angle means that he always has to fetch it. The ball also gets a little big on him and he ends up top-edging it towards short third man, where Farooqi settles under the high ball and completes the catch!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: SO Hetmyer

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: R Ashwin

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: cleans him up with an absolute peach! Sizzling yorker that seems to start on middle and leg stump before swerving away at the last moment. Abhishek is completely flummoxed by it and can't lay bat on it as the ball flattens off stump! What a special delivery!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: MA Agarwal
commentary: holes out to long off! Flighted devilishly on a full length on off stump. Mayank looks to smash it into next week but is beaten in the flight. Like Phillips, he has to reach out for it and toe-ends it miles up into the air towards long off. Buttler settles under it and completes the catch comfortably!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RA Tripathi
commentary: taken excellent at slip! Full delivery just outside off stump. Tripathi takes a step down the track, and opens his bat face, almost guiding it towards Holder, who is stationed at a wide slip. Holder flings himself to his left and holds onto a spectacular catch! But hang on....Tripathi has reviewed this one, saying that he has not nicked it at all. Replays, though, only confirm what we saw first time out. Tripathi has absolutely smashed it, and he now has to walk back!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: HC Brook
commentary: knocks him over! Back of a length delivery on middle and off stump that skids through. Brook tries to cut it but does not have any room to work with. It sneaks past the bat and then crashes into the stumps! Brook's troubled stay comes to an end, and SRH sink further in trouble!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Washington Sundar
commentary: straight up and taken by Hetmyer! Back of a length delivery on middle and leg stump that climbs onto Sundar. He has a hack across the line but because the ball gets big on him, he can only spoon it towards Hetmyer at extra cover! SRH in all sorts of trouble now!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: GD Phillips
commentary: straight to cover! Looped up on a full length outside off stump, and Phillips' eyes light up. He drives at it but is always reaching out for the ball. In the end, he gets it off the toe end and offers a simple catch to Asif!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Abdul Samad

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: AU Rashid
commentary: stumped by a mile! Flighted up nicely on a length outside off stump. Rashid hares down the track but is nowhere close to the pitch of the ball. He has a swish anyway but misses the ball by quite some distance as it rips past the outside edge. Samson does the rest behind the stumps, and SRH are seven down now!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: B Kumar
commentary: cleans him up! Googly on a length on middle and off stump. Kumar has no clue about it and looks to crash it through the off side. The ball rips back into him, cuts him in half and then disturbs the furniture! RR just two wickets away from victory now!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Umran Malik
RG Sharma
commentary: The drop doesn't prove costly. Was a length ball outside off and Rohit pushed at it without moving his feet. The ball seamed away to take the outside edge. Karthik accepted it gleefully

name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: taken at deep third. That's the pressure of two dot balls. Was a length ball at the stumps and Kishan looked to pick it up over square leg only to get an outside edge that flew to Harshal

name: C Green
commentary: bowled 'im! Full and straight, 137.1kph. Green looks to go hard but all he manages is an inside edge. It hit the bat on the full and crashed into the stumps

name: SA Yadav
commentary: short of length outside off. Surya goes for the cut but ends up hitting it straight to Shahbaz at backward point. It was at an awkward height but Shahbaz leapt in the air and took it comfortably

name: N Wadhera
commentary: third time unlucky. Full on the stumps, Wadhera goes for another big hit but fails to get under it this time. Ends up hitting straight towards Kohli at long-on

name: TH David
commentary: huge, huge wicket. Full on the stumps. David goes for the slog sweep but misses it altogether. The ball clatters into the stumps

name: HR Shokeen
commentary: an excellent catch by du Plessis. It was full around off from Harshal, Shokeen looked to chip it over mid-off but du Plessis ran sideways to his left, keeping his eyes on the ball. He judged it perfectly and timed his jump well to pouch it with both hands over his shoulder. Completed the catch by tumbling over

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Slower length ball that is ballooned straight up and David ain't dropping those! Angled across Faf, who is not able to get the pace off the surface. Loses his shape and ends up lofting the ball to long-on.

name: KD Karthik
commentary: Flicked straight to deep square leg and Green has his first IPL wicket! Length on middle, he gets across and gets a good chunk on that. But couldn't find the gap, unfortunately. Tilak makes no mistake.

name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: and right away, Bishnoi finally collars one of the openers! Fullish length ball flighted on fifth stump, Gaikwad goes for a slog sweep over midwicket and the turn away plus some extra bounce produces a top edge that swirls to short third man. Tremendous athletic take by the fielder leaping up to reach high above his head while backpedaling from the edge of the circle.

name: DP Conway
commentary: Krunal and Wood team up to put a leash on Conway! Short ball on the stumps, hustled for pace trying to pull over midwicket, it hangs up in the air long enough for Krunal to charge in off the rope covering 20 yards before putting in a diving effort to latch onto this at ankle height. Superb effort!

name: S Dube
commentary: googly flighted full on leg stump giving it more air again at 93 kph, Dube goes for another booming slog and top edges this spinning away from him with the ball swirling off the bat toward short third man. Very basic catch taken by Wood this time on the ring waiting for the ball to come down at head height.

name: MM Ali
commentary: Moeen charges a good length ball and keeps running to the dugout. Nowhere near the pitch of this googly on middle and it spins past Moeen's heave as well as off stump for a simple stumping by Pooran.

name: BA Stokes
shortText: c Yash Thakur b Avesh Khan
commentary: slower ball fools Stokes at 123 kph on a fullish length on off stump. Stokes goes to heave this over midwicket but skies a top edge to short third on the ring. Simple catch taken by Thakur bending on his haunches.

name: RA Jadeja
commentary: length ball outside leg stump at 143 kph, Jadeja goes to pull and skies this to deep midwicket. Simple catch taken by Bishnoi jogging in from the rope before settling on his knees 10 yards in for a catch on his haunches.

name: MS Dhoni
commentary: Dhoni's innings is short and sweet! Length ball wide outside off on the guideline, tries to repeat his first ball slash over third man for six but comes off the toe and swirls to Bishnoi coming in off the sweeper rope for his second catch of the over, taken on his knees 10 yards in from the rope.

name: KL Rahul
commentary: fullish length ball on middle, Rahul slog sweeps this to wide midwicket. Doesn't come close to getting enough juice on the shot and Gaikwad ranges to his left to take this 15 yards inside the rope at rib height.

name: KR Mayers
commentary: full on off, slog sweeps this flat but picks out deep midwicket five yards inside the rope at head height. A ferocious half-century comes to an abrupt end. Conway hardly had to move for the catch.

name: DJ Hooda
commentary: fullish length on fifth stump, tries to slog this over wide long-on but Stokes covers 15 yards to his right, settles and reaches up to snatch this at head height two yards in from the rope. If he wasn't there it was most likely landing just over the rope for six.

name: KH Pandya
commentary: fullish length on fifth stump, charges and lofts a drive down the ground but doesn't middle it that well, comes off more of the inner half of the bat and picks out Jadeja two yards inside the rope at head height for a basic catch.

name: MP Stoinis
commentary: bullseye! Good length ball on the stumps, Stoinis backs away from leg trying to heave over wide long-on and misses. The ball spins in and leg stump is knocked back just under the bails.

name: N Pooran
commentary: goes for wide yorker again, doesn't get it full enough and Pooran smokes a blistering drive flat to wide long-off. However, he doesn't get the elevation on it. Stokes on the boundary comes in initially before going back and takes a head height catch two yards in from the rope. If he's not there, it's thudding into the ads for six.

name: A Badoni
commentary: full on middle, skies a drive high in the air swirling wide of Dhoni's right. He shuffles over toward the edge of the ring at short third to take a simple catch.

name: DA Warner
commentary: Warner plays on and it's that angled bat that once again has brought about his downfall! On a length just outside off, was 145.5kph that delivery. He shapes for the cut, but the ball is quite close to him. Evetually, a thick inside-edge is all he gets that clatters into his stumps. Delight for Joseph, dismay for Warner.

name: PP Shaw
commentary: Short ball does the trick for Shami! Banged in short, and hurries Shaw, whose weight was forward. He still tries to got for the pull, but can only get a top-edge with the ball ballooning straight up for mid-on to take a comfortable catch.

name: MR Marsh
commentary: Cleans him up, and Shami has his second! Length ball with a bit of shape away from the batter. He looks to push through the off-side, without any foot movement and is caught on the crease. Can only manage a thick inside-edge as the ball rattles his off and middle poles.

name: SN Khan
commentary: Goes for a sweep again, gets a top-edge and Little makes no mistake at deep backward square leg. Slightly slower through the air, outside off. He lines up for that sweep, but can only mistime it this time around. The ball goes high up and Little, I think misjudged the catch initially, but held on.

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: Oh, what a snorter of a delivery first up, and has Tewatia pulled off a blinder at point? Yes,s he has! Banged in short with the line shoulder-high. Rossouw was not expecting this first ball. Fends at it awkwardly with the ball going to point. Tewatia dives forward and seems to have picked put a beauty. The third umpire has been called for, and he deems that has carried clearly into Tewatia's hands. Joseph bowled that at 146kph and Rossouw had no answers.

name: Abishek Porel
commentary: Takes two balls to create an impact! What a bowler, what a cricketer! Fuller, bowled at 94.3kph. Porel plays all around it, and sees his stumps in a mess. Was nowhere near it. Lost his balance, lost his footwork. Can't keep Rashid out of the game for too long.

name: AR Patel
commentary: On a length outside off and Axar hits it straight to David Miller at deep cover. Was in Axar's slot, but he was a touch legside and slightly off-balanced when looking to cream that away. Does not get enough connection and Miller gobbles it up.

name: Aman Hakim Khan
commentary: Nope, not happening twice, says Rashid! Legbreak with a hint of over-spin on the ball. Was just on and around off. He looks for a slog sweep second time around, gets a massive top-edge as the ball goes straight up. Pandya completes a catch at extra cover.

name: WP Saha
commentary: Roaring start in IPL 2023 for Nortje! A 143 kph missile slanting in to Saha, cramps him for room and does him for pace. It is the nip-backer. Saha hops and looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside. The ball goes off his pads and disturbs the stumps. Titans lose their first.

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: Jaffa! Nortje is well and truly making his presence in the IPL! It is a fireball at 148.8 kph. Gill, even in the excellent form that he is in, has no answer to that. It was speared in on a length around off, jags back in a touch. Gill was on the back foot and looks to defend but is beaten by the movement and is knocked over.

name: HH Pandya
commentary: And Khaleel gets the big fish Pandya! This is what Capitals wanted from Khaleel and he has delivered. Lands it on a length and gets it to come back in to off. Pandya is forced to play at that and pushes at it a touch. Ends up getting a thick outside edge and Porel has his first catch in IPL cricket.

name: V Shankar
commentary: Hugeeee appeal, the umpire stays unmoved again! Marsh cannot believe it and asks Warmer to review it. It is the slower one bowled full on middle and leg, Vijay is done in by the lack of pace and is early into his flick and misses the ball. Is hit what seems to be adjacent. The ball tracker confirms the same - three reds! The Arun Jaitley Stadium has just found its voice back.

name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Buttler with a sensational diving catch diving forward after charging in from long-off! Length ball on the wide guideline, Prabhsimran tries to pull this to the leg side but it comes off the toe and pops up over mid-off. Buttler has 25+ yards to cover but never hesitates and makes it almost to the edge of the circle before launching himself forward and pulling off the catch at ankle height. 10/10 on the judge's scorecards by the panel from Russia, Brazili, New Zealand, Lesotho, Panama and Iceland.

name: PBB Rajapaksa
commentary: man down! Rajapaksa is nailed at the non-striker's end by a scorching drive from Shikhar. Full on sixth stump, Shikhar heaves this flat and Rajapaksa can't get out of the way of this as it drills him in the right arm.

name: JM Sharma
commentary: low full toss on fifth stump, charges and tries to slap this over long-off but it comes too low off the bat at ankle height and hangs up for an easy catch taken by Riyan Parag 10 yards in from the rope at chest height.

name: Sikandar Raza
commentary: bullseye! Good length carrom ball darted in at 96 kph on off stump and skids away past a flat-footed poke to flick the outer half of off stump 3/4 of the way up.

name: M Shahrukh Khan
commentary: full in the slot slanted across eighth stump, Shahrukh goes to drive this over long-on but comes more off the toe. Buttler puts in another brilliant effort charging in from the rope 20 yards. The previous catch he took diving head first. This time he slides feet first to get his body under control and takes a knee height catch in front of his chest. Technically very different from his first approach, but equally flawless.

name: YBK Jaiswal
shortText: c sub (MW Short) b Arshdeep Singh
commentary: fullish length ball on sixth stump, drives loosely to extra cover. Basic catch taken at waist height. Fielder didn't have to move left or right. Matthew Short, on as a sub for Rajapaksa who was injured batting, takes the catch sliding forward on his haunches in front of his chest.

name: R Ashwin
shortText: c S Dhawan b Arshdeep Singh
commentary: the Ashwin experiment blows up, but not in the way that Rajasthan were hoping. Length ball on fifth stump, tries to pull this over mid-on but the ball climbs on him and produces a top-edge that floats in the air behind mid-on. Shikhar backpedals 10 yards before taking a catch at chest height.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: somewhat bizarre caught and bowled, but very athletic from Ellis! Good length ball on fourth stump, goes to drive straight and an inside edge comes off the pads and balloons up over short/silly mid-off. Ellis charges forward to corral a sliding take at knee height.

name: SV Samson
commentary: full on fourth stump, tries to muscle this flat over long-off but picks out Matthew Short five yards inside the ring to take a catch at head height. Aussie tag team produces a wicket.

name: D Padikkal
commentary: bullseye! Ellis finally puts Padikkal out of his misery. Preity Zinta is up on her feet on the owner's balcony loving this with big applause. Length ball cross seam at full pace skids past a front foot pull and crashes into middle and off stump 3/4 of the way up.

name: R Parag
commentary: full pace cross-seam delivery in the slot on fifth stump, Parag tries to launch this over long-off but skews it off the splice and it skies toward long-off. Shahrukh Khan comes in 20 yards off the rope and has to wait an eternity for the ball to come down before taking a simple catch.

name: SO Hetmyer
commentary: yorker is spot on fifth stump, jammed out to long-off for one. Hetmyer turns back for a suicide two, but Jurel didn't get the memo and stands pat for one. Hetmyer wanted the strike and winds up near the striker's end before giving up. The relay comes back to Curran, who takes the bails off disdainfully.

name: Rahmanullah Gurbaz
commentary: that is one way to get out. Almost nail the reverse-sweep but find short third with it. This is on a length, outside off, and he middles it with the reverse. Except that he has played it finer than he wants to. Straight to short third

name: VR Iyer
commentary: timber. This has jagged back in to hit the middle stump. He has missed this by a long way. Willey stays on a length, just outside off, Iyer likes to play off the back foot, and tries to muscle it through the off side. The seam movement beats him by six inches at least

name: Mandeep Singh
commentary: and he is already the old batter. How has that hit the off stump? Left-arm quick, hitting the off stump of a right-hand batter usually happens when the ball is swinging back in or if the batter is going hammer and tongs. This one, though, is a wobble-seam delivery that lands on middle and off, seams away to beat Mandeep's defensive prod, and still manages to clip the off stump. Mandeep is squared up

name: N Rana
commentary: big appeal for a catch as Rana reverse-sweeps first ball. Not given on the field, and they review after much discussion. Replays show this has come straight off the glove. Rana shapes up fort the shot early, Bracewell gets some bounce to go past the top of the bat and take the glove to lob up for catch for Karthik

name: RK Singh
commentary: misses out on the fifty but he has played an important hand. Harshal bowls the slower bouncer, Rinku tries to get inside the line to try to go over short fine, but ends up gloving it to the keeper. Shah Rukh Khan gives him a standing applause

name: AD Russell
commentary: and his stay is short. Just one ball long. Russell is looking for a six first ball, and he gets a full enough ball, but he has not been able to connect properly at all. Easy catch for long-off, well off the boundary line. Not even close to a six

name: SN Thakur
commentary: finally Thakur finds a fielder. Siraj also bowls to his field for a change. Wide bouncer with the mid-off up. Thakur goes for the pull but there is no way to control it from that height and that line. Gets a big top edge to long-on. That ends a sensational innings from Thakur

name: V Kohli
commentary: gone, the off stump is plucked! Eden is up in celebration. Kohli went to play across the line, but missed this fullish ball which pitched just outside off. It was flicked from the front of the hand, and turned in nicely enough for Narine to strike in his first over. RCB lose an early wicket in a big chase

name: F du Plessis
commentary: another mystery spinner strikes for KKR! Now du Plessis' turn to be cleaned up. Varun tosses it up a bit, and goes on a slightly shorter side of a length outside off. That was bowled from back of the hand, and hinted to turn in, as du Plessis went for an expansive drive but got an inside edge. RCB's chase gets derailed just after they had started well

name: MG Bracewell
commentary: gloved to short fine! Good catch by Rana tumbling forward. Thakur banged it in short again - this time to the left-hander - and pitched it just about on leg stump. Bracewell pulled, but the extra bounce played a part in him not timing it well. The ball ballooned up for a good take by the KKR captain

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: bowled him again! Once again it's the off stump that is uprooted. From the back of the hand, and on the shorter side of a length. That pitched just outside off, and turned in and bounced nicely enough for the bowler's liking, as Maxwell went swinging hard and across the line, but was completely foxed. He lost his shape, as Varun struck again

name: HV Patel
commentary: another inside edge, and bowled him again! That was quicker from Varun too, and was another googly. That is now four bowleds. Bowls from the back of the hand - and the googly - on a good length outside off. Harshal goes pushing hard, as the turn in finds the gap between his bat and pad. This time it is the middle and leg stumps that are disturbed

name: Shahbaz Ahmed
commentary: picks deep point! That was actually well struck, as Shahbaz went reverse sweeping. The fielder in the deep moved a few steps to right to gobble that. Narine went much fuller this time, angling it into the left-hander, as the ball ended on off stump. Shahbaz rolled his wrists and struck nicely, only to unfortunately find the fielder

name: KD Karthik
commentary: another one finds short third! Suyash strikes again, as the mystery spinners continue to have a roll. This one was full and a bit loopy outside off, inviting the big loft from the batter, with Karthik going for it. The ball took off from the outside edge, and flew to short third's right for a simple take

name: Anuj Rawat
commentary: finds short third! Impact Sub gets his counterpart. Top-edged to the fielder there, as he saw this full delivery tossed up just outside off. It hinted to turn away - as Suyash had good revs on the ball - with Rawat going for the big heave across the line. But he got a top edge, and found the fielder

name: KV Sharma
commentary: An animated appeal by Suyash, and not given. The ball went to the slip fielder after Karn missed his sweep, and KKR review. That was bowled from the back of the hand, on a full length on middle and off. Karn swept but missed, and there looks like no bat involved. Ah, UltraEdge detects a faint bottom edge. But Karn is gone even then, since the ball had carried to slip. So he is given caught, and Suyash has his third

name: Akash Deep
commentary: very good catch by Varun! He ended up where an imaginary midwicket fielder would have been, diving forward to complete the catch. There were two others rushing towards the ball, but Varun kept his eyes on it, not getting distracted by Gurbaz reaching so close to his left. The ball was flirted up right into the clouds, as Deep went heaving at this full ball, only to get a top edge. KKR win by 81 runs

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Anmolpreet Singh
commentary: An appeal for lbw and given out. Faster one - 98.6kph - on middle and leg. Anmolpreet was looking to work it on the leg side but gets beaten and pinged on the back leg. Just above knee roll. He has once again reviewed it and the ball-tracking shows it was just clipping the leg stump. So it's umpire's call and Anmolpreet will have to walk back

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MA Agarwal
commentary: taken at extra cover. On a good length outside off, and Mayank went for the drive on the up. Ended up hitting it in the air. Stoinis leapt and took it overhead with both hands

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: RA Tripathi
commentary: short of length outside off. Tripathi looks to ramp it over short third but there's hardly any pace available to execute that shot. Ends up hitting it to the left of Mishra who dives full length to grab it with both hands

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: AK Markram
commentary: and he has been bowled first ball. Was fired in around off, fuller than good length. Markram went for the drive but the ball spins away just enough to beat the bat and hit the outer half of the off stump. SRH in trouble, and Krunal will be on a hat-trick at the start of his next over

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: HC Brook
commentary: stumped! By a mile. Brook uses his feet once again but Bishnoi has bowled it slightly shorter and outside off. Brook was nowhere near the pitch of the ball. Looks to push at it but gets beaten on the outside edge. An easy stumping for Pooran

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Washington Sundar
commentary: tossed up on the stumps, looked like a googly. Washington's eyes lit up as he looks to clear long-on. Not enough power behind that and Hooda takes at the boundary line

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Abdul Samad

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: AU Rashid
commentary: Mishra picks up his second. Tossed up outside off, 78.5kph. Rashid looks to clear long-off but hardly any power on it. Hooda walks in a couple of steps and accepts it

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Umran Malik
commentary: full and wider outside off. Dragged towards wide long-on. Malik charges back for the second but Hooda throws it on the bounce for Unadkat to break the stumps. Malik was well short

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: B Kumar

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KR Mayers
commentary: taken at deep square leg! Some relief for SRH finally. It's a huge boundary there, and Mayers found the only fielder in the deep on the leg side. It was the third pull shot of the over from Mayers, who saw another good length delivery fired at him. He pulled it hard and flat too, but the boundary was too big for the ball to land beyond it

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KL Rahul
commentary: given out leg before wicket, as Rahul misses his reverse sweep! That looked plumb to the naked eye, but hang on... Rahul has reviewed even as he is walking back. Length ball ball flicked from the front of the hand on leg stump, as it turned away to end around middle. Rahul reverse swept but swung his bat early, with the ball passing his bottom edge. No bat involved there, as he is struck on what seems to be middle stump. Yup, that would have smacked the middle stump, and SRH get a consolation wicket

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: DJ Hooda
commentary: great catch by Bhuvi! No reaction at all from the bowler despite nabbing it one-handed to his left. Bhuvi had to tumble to his left to grab that low, as he stuck his left hand out. He bowled what seemed like a legcutter on a good length on off, with Hooda jumping out again. Hooda ended up fending at it, and giving Bhuvi a catch. SRH fighting here

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KH Pandya
commentary: outside edge, and the keeper takes it low to his left! Good length ball angled into the left-hander from around the wicket, and was very slightly wide of off. Pandya looked to fence that away, but got an outside edge, as the 149kph ball seemed to rush on to him

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MP Stoinis

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: R Shepherd
commentary: given out again, and reviewed again! Now this one was a big-turning googly after he got Rahul with a legspinner. This also looked like heading down leg, as Rashid bowls on a good length on off, only for the ball to end on leg stump. Shepherd was playing on off stump, with a massive gap between bat and pad, with the latter around leg. And guess what, it is umpire's call on clipping the top of leg. That was great turn there

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: N Pooran
YBK Jaiswal
commentary: it's a miracle! AKA, a wicket! Back of a length on middle, Jaiswal comes down the track trying to bully another cross bat shot over the leg side but cramps himself coming too close to the ball and this lobs up off a top edge over the middle of the pitch. Mukesh calls for it and takes a simple catch to end a rollicking opening stand.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: yorker on middle at 134 kph, jammed out back to the bowler. Mukesh fires back at Buttler for a runout chance at the stumps that misses. Warner is appealing for a catch believing this was not a bump ball. Indeed the replays show this was not jammed off into the ground but rather bounced first and came off the toe floating back to Mukesh. He juggled it initially before taking the catch on the rebound. It came back to Mukesh at rib height to his left and he stabbed at it initially to pop it further up into the air before taking it on a second effort. Rather than celebrating a catch though, he fired at the stumps for a runout. It was really Warner who appealed for the catch. Bizarre sequence but Buttler's innings finally ends.

name: SV Samson
commentary: floated full on sixth stump, skies this a mile high but well short of the long-on rope. Nortje has a much less adventurous effort required for this compared to the theatrical drop on the run on the Buttler chance earlier. Just waits for it to come down into his hands at neck height 15 yards in from the rope for a simple catch.

name: R Parag
commentary: bullseye! Full on off stump tailing in a touch. Parag heaves across the line and misses. Middle and off stump are split apart halfway up.

name: PP Shaw
commentary: sensational one-handed catch from Samson! Full on fourth stump, Shaw goes to flick through mid-on, Samson is wrong-footed initially but recovers to fling himself to his right in front of slip and clings onto a low chance at shin height.

name: DA Warner
commentary: good length ball on middle, Warner goes to reverse/switch hit this and misses off the chest while crouching low. Big lbw shout.... Umpire takes five seconds..... and finally raises the finger. Warner goes for DRS immediately. Again, he was hit in the torso after missing the shot, the question is how how was he hit there considering he was crouching low. Ball-tracking shows he was indeed crouched very low, as three reds light up on the projection.

name: MK Pandey
commentary: full and swinging into middle, Pandey is hit low on the shins after he misses a flick and this is stone dead. Pandey turns and walks away before the umpire raises the finger. Warner has a chat with him to cajole him into using a review. Pandey's entire body language shows he knew he was very out. This is going to rub salt into the wound. No way was this missing the stumps. Indeed three full reds show up on ball-tracking with the ball crashing into leg stump after hitting him in front of middle. Delhi lose a review and Boult is on a hat-trick.

name: RR Rossouw
commentary: full on fourth stump, Rossouw goes for one of his bread and butter reverse sweeps, but this comes off more of a toe/cue shot that floats gently to cover on the ring. Sharp catch taken at ankle height diving forward by Jaiswal, who is having a terrific all-round match. Rossouw wanted to play that much more squarer than he did.

name: Lalit Yadav
commentary: drag on! Fullish length ball angled in from around the wicket on fourth stump, Yadav goes for a big heave over midwicket and inside edges this onto his pads before it caroms back gently onto middle stump.

name: AR Patel
commentary: charges down the stumps to a ball dragged much wider outside off and with the length pulled back too. Axar gets nowhere remotely close to this and flails in vain missing badly. Simple stumping.

name: R Powell
commentary: full on the stumps, Powell tries to slog this but gets more wrists than biceps behind this shot trying to adjust to the spin on the carrom ball. It goes high to deep midwicket and a safe catch is taken two yards inside the rope by Hetmyer at chest height.

name: Abishek Porel
commentary: floated full on leg stump, slogs this out to deep midwicket but not much power behind the shot and it floats to Hetmyer coming in 10 yards off the rope, who takes the catch sliding forward on his knees.

name: A Nortje
commentary: bullseye! Slower length ball skids on low toward leg stump at 109 kph, Nortje flails awkwardly over the ball with his shot and the ball pings the outer half of leg stump 3/4 of the way up.

name: RG Sharma
commentary: Terrific delivery from Deshpande. He is pumped. Knocks over the off bail. On a back of a length, angling in, skidding in to breach the defences of Rohit. It straightens fairly late off the seam to square up Rohit and hit the top of off and middle. The bail landed about 5 yards short of the boundary at deep third, says Matt Roller from Wankhede

name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: Holes out to long-on. Jadeja strikes with his fourth ball. Digs it short, angling across off stump, Kishan dares to pull against the angle. He was aiming midwicket, but ends up mis-hitting it to Pretorius at long-on. Jadeja has been taken down by left-handers in the recent past, but this time he takes down Kishan at the Wankhede

name: C Green
commentary: Jadeja holds onto this return catch. Pushed through outside off, on a fuller length, drilled back to Jadeja. The bowler was originally looking to take evasive action or rather throws his hands up in self defence. But he clings onto the return catch in the end. Jadeja and Santner have turned it around for CSK at the Wankhede

name: SA Yadav
commentary: Dhoni thinks he has his man. Not given out caught behind. Dhoni calls for a review almost immediately. Has SKY nicked it? Pushed through flatter and quicker, skidding down the leg side. SKY shapes for a sweep. Seems like SKY has gloved this behind to Dhoni. UltraEdge detects a spike. Another low score for SKY

name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: Jadeja has snagged another left-hander. Umpire Gaffney's finger goes up. Varma challenges the on-field out decision. Even quicker and fizzes off the surface, breaks in to beat the inside edge and strike the front pad below the knee-roll. It would've crashed into leg stump. Varma has to depart

name: Arshad Khan
commentary: Thumps the pad and given out lbw. Varma chats with Arshad and MI decide against a review. Santner gets it to straighten enough from left-arm around and hit the pad in line with middle. The ball lobs off the pad to slip. Great reflexes from Rahane there

name: TH David
commentary: 6,4,6,and out! Deshpande is pumped once again. He has David holing out to Rahane at deep midwicket. Offcutter into the pitch, Deshpande hides it away from David who fetches it and ends up dragging the ball to the outfielder

name: T Stubbs
commentary: Maiden IPL wicket for Sisi. Welcome to the IPL. He takes down his SEC team-mate. Excellent tag-team work at the boundary. Pretorius takes the overhead catch with both hands at the edge of the long-off boundary. He then loses his balance and topples beyond the boundary, but has the presence of mind to lob the ball back to Gaikwad who is in the field of play. Slower full ball from Magala, he takes it away from the swinging arc, Stubbs can only slice it in the air

name: DP Conway
commentary: Chopped-on and Mumbai Indians have struck early! Just what the hosts would have needed. A little bit late on the back of a length ball just outside off. He pushes at it tentatively and ends up inside-edging the ball back onto his stumps. That will get the crowd going.

name: AM Rahane
commentary: Oh, he has flogged that straight to long-on! A hint of turn for Chawla on the length ball outside off. Seems like the ball came a touch slower to Rahane, who was looking to loft it much straighter. Gets it off the bottom of the blade and Suryakumar Yadav makes no mistake coming in.

name: S Dube
commentary: Another chop-on and Dube is a goner! Gets that length ball to skid quickly off the surface, angling into the batter. He stays back looking for a cut, but the ball is quite close to his body. Ends up inside-edging back onto his stumps. Celebrates in his own style, does Kartikeya.

name: WP Saha
commentary: taken this time, brilliantly by Jagadeesan! Full delivery at the stumps and Saha looks to sweep it away. He gets down on one knee but the ball seems to stick in the surface ever so slightly. The ball skews off the top edge and lobs up towards mid wicket, where Jagadeesan runs backwards and completes a superb take!

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: holes out to long on! Length delivery hung outside off stump, and it forces Gill to fetch it. He advances and tries to go over long on but because he has to reach out for it, he ends up chalking it. Umesh settles himself under the high ball at long on, and does the rest!

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: and Sudharsan perishes in that pursuit! Back of a length delivery outside off stump that hurries onto Sudharsan. He comes down the track and looks to clear long off but does not get the power or the elevation. Arrows it straight to Anukul at long off, who makes no mistake!

name: A Manohar
commentary: what a ripper! Googly on a length on off stump. Manohar does not quite pick it and goes searching for it. He leaves a gap between bat and pad, and then sees the ball rip through that gap. It kisses the outside of the front pad before smashing into the stumps! Suyash is over the moon, and why should he not be!

name: Rahmanullah Gurbaz
shortText: c Yash Dayal b Mohammed Shami
commentary: gloves it, and taken by Dayal! Back of a length delivery on leg stump that hurries onto Gurbaz. He has a swipe at it but is late on the stroke, meaning that he eventually gloves it. Bharat and Dayal go for the catch and run into each other, but the latter, somehow, manages to cling on diving forward! The communication system broke down there but Dayal did well to keep his eyes on the prize!

name: N Jagadeesan
commentary: holes out to deep square leg! Length delivery on middle and leg stump. Jagadeesan plants his front foot and gets decent contact on his flick. But he does not go through with his shot and ends up arrowing it straight down Manohar's throat at deep square leg!

name: VR Iyer
commentary: holes out to long on! Joseph breaks open the game again! Full and aimed at the batter's toes. It is not the yorker Joseph was looking for but it cramps Iyer for room just enough. He has a swing at it but can't generate the power or the elevation, hitting it straight down Gill's throat!

name: N Rana
commentary: and he sends Rana packing! Full delivery on middle and off stump. Rana plants his front foot and looks to go over mid off but does not display enough conviction. He has a half-hearted push at it and ends up chipping it straight to Shami at mid off!

name: AD Russell
shortText: c sub (†KS Bharat) b Rashid Khan
commentary: googly on a back of a length on leg stump. Russell has a massive heave at it and seems to miss as the ball pops up off the thigh pad and nestles into the keeper's gloves. Bharat, though, is convinced there is some bat involved and GT, in fact, review! Oh, hello! Looks like there is plenty of merit in that review. Russell has absolutely smashed that off the inside edge into his pad. And Rashid gets the better of Russell, just when his team needed him to!

name: SP Narine
shortText: c sub (J Yadav) b Rashid Khan
commentary: one brings two! Rashid has turned this game on its head! Length delivery on middle and off stump. Narine, sticking to his brief of attacking Rashid, has a mow across the line. He gets a good piece of it but it is not good enough to clear deep mid wicket. The fielder comfortably pouches it, a few yards inside the rope!

name: SN Thakur
commentary: hat-trick for Rashid! Oh my word! This is incredible! Googly on a length on middle and off stump. Just like the other day, Shardul does not pick the googly. Against RCB, he got an inside edge that saved him but today, he does not get any bat as the ball smashes into the pads, right in front of middle and off stump. The umpire raises his finger but Shardul wants to have another look! No bat involved, and three reds on Ball Tracking! Rashid has an IPL hat-trick, and GT inch closer to yet another victory!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: extraordinary finish to the first match and now an extraordinary start to this contest with a wicket first ball! Back of a length delivery nails Prabhsimran above the knee roll but stuck on the crease prodding down the wrong line. He's hit quite high but is deep enough for the umpire to uphold the lbw appeal and Prabhsimran curiously walks straight off without even consulting Shikhar about using a review. It looked quite high on the live shot and the replays too.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: S Dhawan

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: MW Short
commentary: and now it is the carbon copy of the first-ball wicket! Good length swinging into middle past a heave across the line, Short is struck above the knee roll on the back leg but his leg is bent flexing on the shot. This looks pretty dead and Bruce Oxenford gives it out fairly quickly after the appeal from Jansen. Short has a long chat with Shikhar before the time expires on the DRS review clock and he walks off.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: JM Sharma
commentary: fullish length ball on fourth stump at 140 kph, Jitesh tries to drive this on the up aiming to clear mid-off but it wasn't full enough for the shot and miscues this flat to the fielder five yards inside the ring at mid-off, Markram the captain taking a chest height catch with ease.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: SM Curran
commentary: charges a fullish length ball floated wider again on seventh stump but Curran gets nowhere near the pitch and a googly spinning away results in a miscued drive sliced tamely in the air ballooning to short third man. Simple catch taken by Bhuvi shuffling to his left along the edge of the ring.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Sikandar Raza
commentary: bouncer on middle, Raza tries to lean back to ramp this 142 kph ball over deep third man but he doesn't get enough lumber on it and it carries to the man stationed two yards in from the rope, Mayank Agarwal, taken at chest height.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: M Shahrukh Khan
commentary: googly spins in sharply after being flighted on a fullish length at 83 kph on fourth stump, Shahrukh prods down the wrong line and is struck below the knee in front of middle and off. LBW shout upheld. Shahrukh has a brief chat with Shikhar before calling for the review. The only chance he has of being saved is if this was spinning too sharply to miss leg. But ball-tracking shows it is clipping that outside of leg stump with umpire's call keeping it out. But Kings will not lose a review.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Harpreet Brar
commentary: bullseye! Length ball angled into middle stump at 148 kph, Harpreet is just not quick enough getting the bat down in time and this laser destroys middle and leg stump.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RD Chahar
commentary: full on fourth stump, shuffles across to sweep and misses, big lbw shout upheld. This looked iffy live. Chahar calls for a DRS review. Main doubt was whether he was hit in line with off stump or outside the line. He was hit low on the back thigh in the crouching position. Ball-tracking shows impact is "umpire's call" so the decision stays on field.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: NT Ellis
commentary: drag on with a reverse sweep! Great day to be a leggie in the IPL. Googly flighted full on fourth stump spins in, Ellis crouches low trying to reverse paddle this behind point and it comes off the glove, then the thigh onto the stumps. Bizarre shot to play when Shikhar is begging for someone to hang with him.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Mohit Rathee

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: HC Brook
commentary: bullseye! Slower ball knuckle ball angled in from around the wicket at 117 kph on a good length. Brook is through his drive too early and is beaten through the gate. Leg stump cartwheels out of the ground.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: MA Agarwal
commentary: flighted on a fullish length on fifth stump, he has to reach a long way forward trying to slog this and winds up skying this a mile high toward Curran at long-on. Curran comes in a touch too far stepping in 10 yards from the rope before taking three steps back and swiveling sideways to take this at rib height before falling to the turf to soften the catch with gravity pulling it back sharply to earth.

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RA Tripathi

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: AK Markram
V Kohli
commentary: finds deep midwicket! Mishra strikes in his first over. Kohli looked to pull this short ball, but didn't really get the ideal bounce off the pitch. Looked it was the wrong 'un, as it angled down middle and leg. Mishra breaks through for LSG, as RCB are checked

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: the leg stump is uprooted! That was launched at 150kph, though Maxwell's bat swing seemed quicker still. Good length ball on middle and off, and angles in. Maxwell is too early into his heave across the line, and is completely blown by the pace and movement. But what an innings!

name: KR Mayers
commentary: Castled! It's the sweet sound of timber and Siraj is pumped! Bangs it in back of a length on middle, goes across this time but cramps him for room and Mayers chops on. He is the form player and that's a good early wicket for RCB

name: KL Rahul
commentary: And Siraj strikes immediately! KL Rahul picks out deep square! Full on leg and he looked to flick it away. Doesn't get the connection he wanted and it's straight to Kohli, who is thrilled after taking the catch. Rahul falls for 18 off 20 and I am sure he will come in for some slack after this knock!

name: DJ Hooda
commentary: Has he edged that? Dinesh Karthik thinks so and RCB review immediately. Full on middle and going across him, Hooda had a little push at it. He is walking even before the review is completed. And UltraEdge confirms that there was bat on that! Dinesh Karthik took a good low catch to his right and he knew straight away. Parnell has his first of the season!

name: KH Pandya
commentary: And the swing brings another wicket for Parnell! Pitches it up outside off again and this time Krunal gets the edge and DK makes no mistake! What a first over for Parnell!

name: MP Stoinis
commentary: Karn Sharma has his revenge! Brave of him to toss it up outside off again. Stoinis goes for the drive again but ends up slicing it up to deep point where Shahbaz makes no mistake despite a slight wobble! He is thrilled. Stoinis walks back having played a blinder here!

name: N Pooran
shortText: c Shahbaz Ahmed b Mohammed Siraj
commentary: Full toss on leg and Pooran picks out deep backward square! This will be checked for height on the full toss, though. And it will be an umpire review as it's a catch. Pooran looked to flick that away behind square, but spooned a catch to Shahbaz Ahmed in the deep. Ball-tracking shows that was fine and Pooran has to go! Siraj has got the key wicket of Pooran, but is this too late for RCB?

name: A Badoni
commentary: Badoni gets a six, but it won't count be cause his bat has crashed into the stumps! Badoni moves across to scoop this behind. Nailed the shot, but his right hand came off the bat and the toe-end just hit the stumps! Oh my! What drama

name: JD Unadkat
commentary: Holes out at long-on! Banged in short and Unadkat went for the pull. Picks up Faf du Plessis, who takes it reverse-cupped before switching it to a more normal hold

name: MA Wood
commentary: Harshal castles Wood! It's that dipping slower ball and it has done Wood in! Crashes into middle-stump!

name: DA Warner
commentary: Caught at short third by Meredith. Slower legcutter, floated on leg stump, Warner slogs early and top-edges it to short third. Warner isn't happy with himself once again. It has been that kind of a day for DC's captain

name: PP Shaw
commentary: down on one knee, and swept straight at backward square leg! That's risk and reward in a nutshell, tossed up and swept hard, but can't find the gap. A vital breakthrough for Mumbai

name: MK Pandey
commentary: down the track and lofted to long-off! Pandey took on the legbreak with a skip to the pitch, but he didn't quite get there, and the lanky Behrendorff was well placed back on the rope to end a promising knock

name: YV Dhull
commentary: well held, running back at deep midwicket! Dhull took on the shorter ball with a flick off the hip but didn't get enough bat through the stroke! Wadhera watched it well, stayed inside the rope as he gathered over his shoulder, and that's a timely breakthrough for Mumbai

name: R Powell
commentary: another wrong'un, the finger goes up. This looks plumb but Capitals have asked for a review of the on-field out decision. Tossed up nice and full, breaks back in to beat the inside edge and ping the front pad below the knee-roll in line with middle. Ball-tracking indicates that it would've cannoned into leg stump

name: Lalit Yadav
commentary: Chawla breaches the defences of Lalit. The leg stump is knocked out. Chawla dangles up another wrong'un, Lalit goes searching for a drive, and is bowled through the gate. This has been a fine shift from Chawla

name: AR Patel
commentary: Behrendorff has Axar holing out to deep square. Too full and on the pads, Axar picks it up with his wrists but hits it straight to Arshad Khan. He goes for 54 off 25 balls. Terrific effort with the bat from Axar

name: Abishek Porel
commentary: down the track and holes out to Green at mid-off. Porel gives Benrendorff the charge. The left-arm seamer drags his length back and hits the bat as opposed to bat hitting ball. Spliced to Green who is right at the edge of the circle

name: Kuldeep Yadav
commentary: short and at the body, Kuldeep fends it into the leg side and takes off for a risky single. Wadhera swoops down on the ball from short midwicket and flips it back to the stumps at the non-striker's end. Sharp work from Wadhera

name: A Nortje
commentary: Meredith knocks out the leg stump. Nortje gives Meredith the charge once again. But Meredith nails the yorker and the stumps this time

name: RG Sharma
commentary: Whoa! Sensational catch from Porel. He throws himself to his right and comes out with the ball in his right hand. Given out caught behind. Rohit has asked for a review. Wide yorker from Mustafizur. Rohit jams his bat down on the ball. Not a bump ball. Ultra Edge confirms it. Superbly taken by Porel. Top decision from umpire Gough. Rohit throws his head back and drags himself off the field

name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: pressed into the off-side, and there's the breakthrough! Rohit wanted to get Ishan off-strike to the spinner, and he did so with greater emphasis than he had intended! Ishan was ball-watching as his skipper charged through, point gathered to fling to the non-striker's end and he's not even in the frame! Yadav gathered well, meeting the third umpire's approval.

name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: pitched-up delivery on off stump, another slot delivery angling into Tilak. But this time he slices it off the toe end to Pandey at deep midwicket

name: SA Yadav
shortText: c Kuldeep Yadav b Mukesh Kumar
commentary: SKY falls for another first-ball duck. Caught at the edge of the fine-leg boundary. Short ball veering down the leg side, SKY picks it up and hits it straight to Kuldeep. This over started with 4,6,6. It ends with a double-strike

name: YBK Jaiswal
commentary: Deshpande strikes and Jaiswal is out of here! It's an excellent back of a length ball, angling away outside off. Jaiswal had his weight on the back foot and looks to heave it to the on side. Ends up getting it high on the bat and slices it towards mid-off where Dube makes no error.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Buttler loses his off stump! Tosses it up generously and lands it on a length outside off. Dips enough to pass under Buttler's attempted swipe across the line. Uproots the off stump and Moeen has his sweet revenge.

name: D Padikkal
commentary: Jadeja gets Padikkal! An impressive little knock ends prematurely. Tosses it up and lands it on a length outside off, he has to fetch the sweep from outside off. Ends up top-edging it straight to Conway at deep backward square leg. The 77-run stand ends.

name: SV Samson
commentary: Jaffa from Jadeja and Samson has to walk back! What a ball that. He bowls it on a length around off and middle and gets it to straighten just enough. There good bounce on that and Samson has no time to adjust and gets beaten on the outside comprehensively. The noise at Chepauk is deafening!

name: R Ashwin
commentary: And that's that for Ashwin with the bat tonight! Goes back and across to the length ball. He looks to heave it over mid-off but ends up skying it straight to Magala there. Magala hurt his finger while taking that.

name: DC Jurel
commentary: Another full toss, Akash ends up dismissing Jurel. He skies it high and long-off comes in to pouch that easily. The umpires want to check the height of the ball and it is well below the waist.

name: JO Holder
commentary: Holder finds deep midwicket to perfection! Slower one again, the offcutter at 123 clicks. Holder goes back and heaves across the line but finds Conway stationed there.

name: A Zampa
commentary: Theekshana drops a sitter but Zampa is run-out! He scoops it high to short fine leg but he runs around and drops it. Regathers and throws it to Dhoni, who underarms a throw at the stumps. Royals have 175 on the board.

name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: Straight up, goes very high and Jaiswal has taken a very good catch! Length ball with just a hint of shape away from Gaikwad, who closes the face of the bat a touch too early. Takes the leading edge of his blade and balloons straight up. Jaiswal runs in from cover, calls early and takes the catch, rather comfortably.

name: DP Conway
commentary: Conway departs and things are looking even tougher for CSK now! Tossed up outside off, Conway looks to go over cover but the angle meant he could not reach it properly. Ends up skewing it straight up as Jaiswal backtracks from extra cover and completes a well-judged catch.

name: AM Rahane
commentary: Loud, loud appeal as Rahane misses and is rapped on the pads! The umpire agrees and Ashwin is over the moon. Pre-meditated slog sweep from Rahane, but Ashwin pushed that carrom ball through and on middle and leg. Rahane misses and once that happened it was always going to be trouble. He does not opt for the review. Wasn't too impressed by his shot.

name: S Dube
commentary: Oh, what a bowler, Ashwin! Now, gets the one that fizzes quickly into the pads of Dube. He was just not expecting it and is caught plumb in front of the stumps. The umpire's finger is up in a flash and Dube does not review.

name: MM Ali
commentary: Oh, that's an excellent catch from Sandeep Sharma running across from deep backward square leg. Tossed up ball on middle stump. Moeen goes for the slog sweep, but does not get it anywhere close to the middle. I thought he had placed it well but Sandeep sprinted across so well.

name: AT Rayudu
commentary: Another one bites the dust! Rayudu makes no impact whatsoever. Short of a length ball on middle and leg. He romps back looking to clear the field, but does not get it off the middle. Hetmyer runs to his right from deep midwicket and completes an excellent catch. They are catching everything, are RR and CSK are losing the plot.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Prabhsimran Singh
shortText: c Rashid Khan b Mohammed Shami
commentary: Shami gets a wicket second ball! Innocuous back of a length ball on the hips of Prabhsimran who was looking for a flick. But the ball hits the high part of his blade and lobs straight to Rashid at short midwicket, who takes a simple catch.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: S Dhawan
commentary: Huge, huge wicket for Titans as Dhawan departs! Good length ball on middle and leg, he shimmies down the track looking to loft it over mid-on. The bat turns in his hands a touch and he ends up ballooning it straight up. Alzarri Joseph runs back from mid-on and ends up taking a comfortable. So, the man who has been scoring all the runs for Kings has to go. Hardik is elated!

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: MW Short
commentary: Wrong'un that beats Short all ends up, and sees his stumps in a mess! Flatter into Short, who was looking to swipe that away. Does not pick the googly, and the ball clatters into middle and leg stump. Rashid gets the better of his Adelaide Strikers team-mate

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: PBB Rajapaksa
commentary: End of a difficult innings for Rajapaksa! Knee-high full toss on middle stump, Rajapaksa chips it straight to deep midwicket. Easy catch for Gill running in. The batter never got going and a strike rate of 76.92 was just not good enough on the day.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: JM Sharma
commentary: Edged, is it? Saha appeals but does not get a lot of support. Pandya has taken a review in the nick of time. They are already a review down. Back of a length ball just on off that tails away from Jitesh just a touch. He pushes at it and the ball goes past his outside edge. Oh, hello. UltraEdge confirms there was a smidge of an edge on that. What a top review from Saha, who was the only appealing. The on-field umpire has to change his decision, and Kings are four down.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: SM Curran
commentary: And, now Curran falls! Mohit gets his second wicket of the night. He goes into the pitch with the off-cutter shoulder high with the line outside off. Curran has to wait for it, and while he gets a good chunk on it, there is no pace. The ball goes straight to deep midwicket where Gill takes a simple catch.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: M Shahrukh Khan
commentary: Fuller and outside off, he spanks it to the right of mid-off. There is a bit of misfield and Shahrukh goes for the second. But Miller throws a flat throw to the keeper who whips off the bails in a flash and finds Shahrukh short of his crease. Never run on a misfield as they say, and that has cost PBKS a wicket.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Harpreet Brar

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: R Dhawan
commentary: Oh, what a bit of work from Saha. Has he run out Brar last ball off the innings? Yes, he has. Fuller length ball outside leg stump as Brar backs away looking to flay it away. Gets a thick inside-edge with the ball going to the right of Saha, who puts in a dive to first stop the ball. He then gets up and fires in a throw, gloves on. Hits the top of the stumps and finds Dhawan short.

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: WP Saha
commentary: 100th IPL wicket for Rabada! Rabada sticks with the short ball strategy and Saha goes for another pull, but this time he picks out deep square leg! Short takes it above head-height and Saha has to walk

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: Shubman Gill
commentary: Cleaned him up! Is this too late for a late twist? It's full on off and angles in just enough to hit off-stump as Gill swings and gets an inside edge. Late, late twist? Sign me up!

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: B Sai Sudharsan
shortText: c Prabhsimran Singh b Arshdeep Singh
commentary: And Arshdeep has the breakthrough! Bangs it in short on off, Sai Sudharsan swivels and pulls but gets a top edge and it goes straight to deep fine leg!

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: HH Pandya
commentary: Brar gets Hardik! He clears his front leg and wants to go big down the ground but doesn't quite time it. Picks out Sam Curran who takes it reverse-cupped. He lets out a little roar as the Titans skipper walks back

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: DA Miller

venue: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium, Mohali, Chandigarh
name: R Tewatia
MA Agarwal
commentary: and he picks up a wicket first ball. Was short of length around off. Agarwal was on the move, and was cramped. He looked to steer it away only to get an outside edge to Varun at short third

name: RA Tripathi
commentary: Russell has two in the over, he started celebrating even before Gurbaz completed the catch. Was a bouncer at 136.9kph. Just outside off. Tripathi went for the pull only to top-edge it straight up. Gurbaz finished the catch to his left, still behind the stumps

name: AK Markram
commentary: Fuller around off, goes on one knee to clear the deep midwicket boundary only to be caught by Russell near the boundary line. 72-run stand has been broken!

name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: Length ball around off, Abhishek looks to go big but doesn't get the distant, Thakur runs in from long-on and completes the catch just outside the ring

name: Rahmanullah Gurbaz
commentary: taken at deep third. Full outside off, and Gurbaz looks to go over extra cover. But he fails to middle it and ends up slicing towards deep third where Umran Malik takes a straightforward catch

name: N Jagadeesan
commentary: taken at deep midwicket. Glenn Phillips, the substitute, with the catch. Was full on the stumps. Jagadeesan went for the slog sweep, connected it alright but ended up hitting straight to the fielder

name: VR Iyer
commentary: a soft dismissal. Length ball on the pads. Iyer looked to hit it over the leg side but ended up getting a leading edge towards long-on. Markram came in a few steps and pouched it

name: SP Narine
